  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nPresently the op pool throws attester slashings into blocks without any regard for profit maximisation (by maximising the number of slashed validators).\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v0.2.4-93b7c3b7\r\nBLS Library: blst\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nWe take valid slashings in no particular order: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/fdc6e2aa8ec5aeeba6740b85df1d284caad526fa/beacon_node/operation_pool/src/lib.rs#L195-L252\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nWe should choose the two best attester slashings! Although there's only two of them, this is an instance of the max cover problem for attestations! I can't believe it took me this long to notice :O\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nImplement a maximum-coverage-based optimiser for attester slashings, using the existing trait in https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/operation_pool/src/max_cover.rs\r\n\r\n",
